---
title:  Turkey, Tomato & Cheddar Chopped Salad  with Cucumber, Honey Mustard Dressing & Toasted Panko
description: The classic turkey club sandwich gets a salad makeover in this quick and easy meal that’s perfect for lunch or dinner. Hearty sliced turkey breast is tossed with cucumber, tomato, and cheddar cheese in a flavorful honey Dijon dressing. Toasted buttery panko breadcrumbs add delightful crunch and depth to every bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/664cadcf5e4dc3c6a6a94152-13271280.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/664cadcf5e4dc3c6a6a94152-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/turkey-tomato-and-cheddar-chopped-salad-664cadcf5e4dc3c6a6a94152
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 22 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1290 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: North America
time required: 15 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1%unit}; roughly chop. Dice @tomato{1%unit} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1⁄4-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}. Dice @sliced turkey breast{8%ounce} into 1-inch pieces.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}.

Add lettuce, tomato, cucumber, scallions, turkey, and @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} to bowl with dressing; toss until evenly combined.

> TIP: Separate any pieces of turkey sticking together before tossing.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide salad between #bowls{} and sprinkle with toasted panko. Serve.